   <concept id="FAR_44_402"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">44.402</ph> Policy requirements.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2600e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2626e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Contractors and subcontractors
at all tiers shall, to the maximum extent practicable:</p>
               <ol id="d2600e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2626e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Be
required to incorporate <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial
products, commercial <?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 44.402 by—
a. Removing from paragraph (a)(1) the words “commercial items” and adding “commercial products, commercial services,” in its place;?>services,</ph> or nondevelopmental items as
components of items delivered to the Government; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2626e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Not be
required to apply to any of its divisions, subsidiaries, affiliates,
subcontractors or suppliers that are furnishing <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial products or
commercial <?FM MARKER [Why] b. Removing from paragraph (a)(2) introductory text the phrase “commercial items or commercial components” and adding “commercial products or commercial services” in its place;?>services</ph> any clause, except those-</p>
                     <ol id="d2600e42" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d2626e39" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Required
to implement provisions of law or <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>Executive orders applicable
to subcontractors furnishing commercial products or <?FM MARKER [Why] c. Removing from paragraph (a)(2)(i) the phrase “executive orders applicable to subcontractors furnishing commercial items or commercial components” and adding “Executive orders applicable to subcontractors furnishing commercial products or commercial services” in its place;?>commercial services;</ph> or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d2626e50" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Determined
to be consistent with customary commercial practice for the item
being acquired.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2626e55" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The clause
at <xref href="52.244-6.dita#FAR_52_244_6"
                        base="i1048410"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.244-6</xref>, Subcontracts
for <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph ">Commercial Products
and Commercial Services,</ph> implements the policy in paragraph
(a) of this section. Notwithstanding any other clause in the prime
contract, only those clauses identified in the clause at <xref href="52.244-6.dita#FAR_52_244_6"
                        base="i1048410"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.244-6</xref> are required
to be in subcontracts for <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial
products or commercial <?FM MARKER [Why] d. Removing from paragraph (b) the terms “Commercial Items” and “commercial items or commercial components” and adding “Commercial Products and Commercial Services” and “commercial products or commercial services” in their places, respectively; and?>services.</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2626e74" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> Agencies
may supplement the clause at <xref href="52.244-6.dita#FAR_52_244_6"
                        base="i1048410"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.244-6</xref> only
as necessary to reflect agency unique statutes applicable to the acquisition
of <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial products
and commercial <?FM MARKER [Why] e. Removing from paragraph (c) the words “commercial items” and adding “commercial products and commercial services” in its place.?>services.</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
